What you need to know:

The game in the San Siro is between the top two in Serie A last season when Juventus won a ninth consecutive league title just one point ahead of InterAs Antonio Conte's Inter and Andrea Pirlo's Juve battle it out, Milan have a chance to increase their advantage at the half-way point this season as they travel to struggling CagliariThe clash is between a team with the best attack in the league, with Inter scoring 43 goals, against the one with the tightest defence with 16 goals conceded